<paragraph id="B58AE1AFA056C4B78552F00825F33D75" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
(Figure 
<figureCitation id="90816CE2CF44931EB3198406281C8902" captionStart="Figure 56" captionStartId="F56" captionText="Figure 56. Distribution of Solanum villosum Mill." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.123.31738.figure56" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/305355" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">56</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName id="FF8664CAABEC9C0F82F89A819436F89C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum villosum" order="Solanales" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosum">
<emphasis id="96856B971B010DF6D4235923B4F7B07C" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Solanum villosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to Europe where it is very common around the Mediterranean basin, the Arabian Peninsula to dry sub-tropical Asia, and eastern Africa (where it is cultivated for its fruit); the species is locally introduced but not persistent and not yet naturalised in North America.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C52283C57BBE28DAB84D5BCE07957186" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3240862" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.123.31738.figure56" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/305355" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" start="Figure 56" startId="F56">
